Package com.w10.risk_game.controllers

Class GameEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.w10.risk_game.controllers.GameEngine
  • public class GameEngine
extends Object
    The GameEngine class is responsible for managing the game map, players, issuing orders, executing orders and their interactions in a game.

      • checkIfOrdersCanBeExecuted

        public boolean checkIfOrdersCanBeExecuted()

        Returns:
        The method is returning a boolean value.

      • executePlayerOrders

        public boolean executePlayerOrders()
        The function executes orders for each player, assigns reinforcements, and updates the current player.
        Returns:
        The method is returning a boolean value. If the execution of player orders is successful, it returns true. If an exception occurs during execution, it returns false.
